cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with high-throughput fluorescence microscopy imaging for protein localization in human cells. The use of Deep Learning models such as GoogleNet and Resnet also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The incorporation of segmentation maps in the proposed classification model also indicates that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of Twin U-Net (TUNet) as a novel classification model suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
